This is the complete, master UX specification for:

Vector by Vektra
Hosted on Vercel
Database on Supabase (Postgres)
Manual-entry first → Network-enabled → Scalable



# B) PRODUCT UX SPECIFICATION (Claude-Ready)

---

## Navigation (Bottom Tabs)

1. Command
2. Enter
3. Matchups
4. Trajectory

Dark-first. No extra screens.

---

## 1. Command Screen

* Rating (large numeric)
* 90-day Win %
* Compounding Index
* Drift Score
* Last Match summary
* Edit timer (if active)
* Upcoming Match Probability

No scrolling required.

---

## 2. Enter Screen (Fast After Play)

Flow:

1. Select Partner (autocomplete + recent chips)
2. Select Opponent 1 & 2
3. WIN / LOSS toggle
4. Game scores (numeric keypad auto-advance)
5. Submit

Total target time: < 60 seconds.

---

## 3. Matchups Screen

Search bar (Pro feature)

Displays:

* Player rating
* Rating confidence
* Head-to-head stats
* Win probability
* Volatility band

Free users see limited version + quiet Pro gate.

---

## 4. Trajectory Screen

Segmented control:

* 10 Games (default)
* 7 Days
* 1 Month

Primary:

* Rating slope chart

Under-chart stats:

* Win %
* Record
* Point differential

No extra graphs.

---

## 5. Admin UX

* Void match
* Merge players
* Edit identity
* Audit log view
* Trigger recompute

All actions audited.

---

